Introduction

Overview: In this lab, we will begin to practice with some of the basic components of ArcGIS Pro. We will be working with a variety of geospatial data types to make a simple map of the Town of Amherst and do some very basic geospatial analyses. The data and maps you generate in this lab may be used again in future labs so be sure to organize, name, and save everything properly. 

Learning goals:
Using the Virtual Computing Lab (VCL) to access ArcGIS Pro 
Using the F: Drive for file management
